# Code owners for pg_lake
#
# Order matters: the last matching pattern for a changed file wins, so the
# broad default sits at the top and the per-area rules below override it.
# Listed owners are automatically requested for review on any PR that
# touches a matching path. See:
# https://docs.github.com/articles/about-code-owners
#
# We keep two owners per area instead of the whole team on every PR: enough
# for one to be available without pinging everyone on every change. Owners
# are the people with the most history in each area (see `git log <path>`),
# balanced so the review load is spread across the team.
